article.description: — Will Carius socred 21 points and Cameron Burrell posted a double-double and Western Illinois downed Denver 82-75 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Carius scores 21 to carry W. Illinois over Denver 82-75
article.linkText: Carius scores 21 to carry W. Illinois over Denver 82-75
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- — Will Carius scored 21 points and Cameron Burrell posted a double-double and Western Illinois downed Denver 82-75 on Saturday night. Burrell finished with 13 points and 13 rebounds for Western Illinois (7-12, 5-7 Summit League), which won its fifth straight game. Ramean Hinton and Adam Anhold each scored 10. Kobey Lam scored 17 points for the Pioneers (2-15, 1-9), Jase Townsend added 15 and Eric Moenkhaus 12. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
